@page "/help"

<PageTitle>User Guide - Super Investor</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="mb-4">Super Investor User Guide</h1>

    <SuperCard Title="Getting Started">
        <h3>Creating an Account</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Visit the Super Investor homepage.</li>
            <li>Click on the "Register" button in the top right corner.</li>
            <li>Fill out the required information and follow the prompts to complete your registration.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Logging In</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Click on the "Login" button in the top right corner.</li>
            <li>Enter your email and password.</li>
            <li>Click "Log in" to access your account.</li>
        </ol>
    </SuperCard>

    <SuperCard Title="Navigating the Platform">
        <h3>Home Page</h3>
        <p>The home page provides an overview of your recent research and quick access to key features. For new users, it offers guidance on how to get started.</p>

        <h3>Search Functionality</h3>
        <p>Use the search bar at the top of the page to look up companies by their ticker symbol or name.</p>
    </SuperCard>

    <SuperCard Title="Researching Companies">
        <h3>Viewing Company Information</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Search for a company using the search bar.</li>
            <li>Click on the company name to view its profile.</li>
            <li>You'll see an overview of the company, including recent filings and financial information.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Accessing Filings</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>On the company page, you'll find a list of recent filings categorized by type (e.g., Financials, Prospectuses, Ownership).</li>
            <li>Click on a filing to view its full content.</li>
        </ol>
    </SuperCard>

    <SuperCard Title="Taking Notes">
        <p><strong>Note:</strong> Note-taking functionality is available for Pro subscribers only.</p>

        <h3>Adding a Note</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>While viewing a filing, select the text you want to annotate.</li>
            <li>An "Add Note" button will appear on the right side of the screen.</li>
            <li>Click the "Add Note" button to open the note-taking card.</li>
            <li>Type your note in the provided text area.</li>
            <li>Click "Save" to add your note.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Viewing and Editing Notes</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Your notes will appear in the right sidebar of the filing view.</li>
            <li>To edit a note, click on the note text.</li>
            <li>Make your changes and click "Save" to update the note.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Deleting Notes</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>To delete a note, click on the note in the sidebar.</li>
            <li>Click the "Delete" button and confirm your action.</li>
        </ol>
    </SuperCard>

    <SuperCard Title="Sharing Research">
        <h3>Sharing an Entire Research Document</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>While viewing a filing with your notes, look for the "Share Research" button.</li>
            <li>Click the button to generate a shareable link.</li>
            <li>Copy the link and share it with others.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Sharing a Specific Note</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>In the notes sidebar, find the note you want to share.</li>
            <li>Click on the "Share" icon next to the note.</li>
            <li>Copy the generated link and share it with others.</li>
        </ol>
    </SuperCard>

    <SuperCard Title="Exporting Notes">
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the company page for which you want to export notes.</li>
            <li>Look for the "Export Notes" button.</li>
            <li>Click the button to download your notes in CSV format.</li>
        </ol>
    </SuperCard>

    <SuperCard Title="Upgrading to Pro">
        <p>To access advanced features like note-taking and sharing:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Click on the "Upgrade" button in the top navigation bar.</li>
            <li>Review the available plans and features.</li>
            <li>Select your desired plan and follow the prompts to complete your subscription.</li>
        </ol>
    </SuperCard>

    <SuperCard Title="Getting Help">
        <p>If you need further assistance:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Check our <a href="/faq">FAQ page</a> for answers to common questions.</li>
            <li>Contact our support team at <a href="mailto:support@superinvestor.com">support@superinvestor.com</a>.</li>
        </ul>
    </SuperCard>
</div>
